(5204, 1, '2016-11-03 07:39:20', '2016-11-03 07:39:20', '<span class="lead">Improved health outcomes depend on good clinical data. UgandaEMR, was the first patient medical records system in Uganda. It was first piloted in 2011 in about 20 health facilities across the country. </span><br><br>\r\nUgandaEMR is built on OpenMRS which is an open source system. The System is currently installed in about 356 health facilities across the country. Most of the general hospitals, HC IV, HC III and some HC II are running the system.\r\nSee Tools section of this site to view a Demo on the UgandaEMR system.\r\n<img src="http://127.0.0.1/emr/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/openmrs.png" width="1463" height="491" srcset="http://127.0.0.1/emr/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/openmrs.png 1463w, http://127.0.0.1/emr/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/openmrs-300x101.png 300w, http://127.0.0.1/emr/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/openmrs-768x258.png 768w, http://127.0.0.1/emr/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/openmrs-1024x344.png 1024w" class="so-widget-image">', 'About EMR', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-emr', '', '', '2016-11-05 06:47:07', '2016-11-05 06:47:07', '', 0, 'http://127.0.0.1/emr/?page_id=5204', 0, 'page', '', 0),
